<br>
And for the Druid that mentioned that the piece of the Shaman epic that you NEED a mage to accomplish--you're right.  You need one or two level 49 mages (level 49 fire pet) to kill this guy.  I won't even comment on the FG analogy and yeah we are great at cleaning up greenies--Wheee.  Great for twinking OTHER classes (anything really usefull for the mage seems to drop off boss or high-end mobs).  How does this address the upper end game and our usefullness.  <br>
<br>
For a lot of upper end guilds that occassionally NEED the distinct abilities that the mage can bring to the table it is very easy for them to produce an alt and PL them to the appropriate level and whip him out when the NEED arises.  Under MOST circumstances we do not bring enough versatility/utility or firepower.  Every class has problems in the upper end game. Accept for clerics--never can seem to get enough clerics, but given game dynamics (how high-end mobs are most effectively overcome, game mechanics (pathing/mobs attacking through walls/AoE attacks through walls/lack of proper pet controls...)/game psychology (how people are jaded against mages in groups or raids)--we are at a distinct disadvantage.<br>
<br>
Am I envious--NO.  I started an Enchanter and a Druid and enjoy them both.  However, I have invested a great deal of time into my mage and I am disappointed.  It is very possible to be disappointed without being envious.  Most of the mages on this board love their mages and want an upgrade to provide a distinct purpose (most believe their distinct purpose should be damage. Thus the desire to upgrade pet damage output and a marginal increase in nuking power).  <br>
<br>
If you've ever sat in a group when it is being put together and they are looking for another damage dealer and you hear (/ooc lvl 57 mage lfg) then you say &quot;Get the mage&quot;.  They say &quot;nah&quot;.  Then 15 minutes later you hear (/ooc lvl 54 monk/rogue/warrior lfg).  Everyone else in the party says &quot;Hey get that rogue/monk/warrior&quot;.  Then you'll know what I mean--even if there is a MT in the group already.  People would rather sit with an empty slot than get another mage, waiting for a more damaging/purposeful class.  I would like to see this change.<br>
